    public abstract class MoveableCharacter
extends javax.swing.JComponent
    This class represents a character in the game which has the ability to move.

    Sitton

      abstract void draw(java.awt.Graphics g) 
      int getCurrentYSpeed(Surface[] surfaces)
      This method makes the character move downwards if it is not standing on a Surface or if it is not in the middle of a jump This method determines the current Y speed of the MoveableCharacter.

      If it's trying to jump this method will return the speedY field.
      If it's standing on a surface this method will return 0.
      If it's not jumping and not standing on the ground, this method will return the constant falling speed.

      void TryToJump()
      This method changes the isJumping field to be true for a short time, thus making the getCurrentYSpeed(Surface[]) method return the jumping speed of the MoveableCharacter, which makes it move upwards for that short amount of time.

      note - if the MoveableCharacter is already in the middle of a jump or is not standing on a Surface, this method will do nothing.

      • TryToJump

        public void TryToJump()
        This method changes the isJumping field to be true for a short time, thus making the getCurrentYSpeed(Surface[]) method return the jumping speed of the MoveableCharacter, which makes it move upwards for that short amount of time.

        note - if the MoveableCharacter is already in the middle of a jump or is not standing on a Surface, this method will do nothing.
        See Also:
        isJumping, onTheGround, getCurrentYSpeed(Surface[])

      • getCurrentYSpeed

        public int getCurrentYSpeed(Surface[] surfaces)
        This method makes the character move downwards if it is not standing on a Surface or if it is not in the middle of a jump This method determines the current Y speed of the MoveableCharacter.

        If it's trying to jump this method will return the speedY field.
        If it's standing on a surface this method will return 0.
        If it's not jumping and not standing on the ground, this method will return the constant falling speed.
        Parameters:
        surfaces - - the surfaces in the JFrame.
        Returns:
        - the correct y speed of the MoveableCharacter according to its current state
        See Also:
        Surface, WorldConstants.PHYSICS.FALLING_SPEED

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        true if the two MoveableCharacters are touching. false if not.
